So, if I, kind of, break this bread, maybe we can share this now a little bit here.
We'll start a little piece here,
and I'm going to take a little piece here --
I think I'd better taste it myself before you have it at lunch.
I'll leave you with what I call the baker's blessing.
May your crust be crisp, and your bread always rise.
